(134, 44, 60, 'Fire Safety Awareness Training Courses', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Following the introduction of the new Regulatory Reform (fire safety) Order 2005 all companies are obliged to ensure that employees receive adequate training in fire safety on a yearly basis. Our course allows companies to keep employees aware of all the key information regarding fire safety in the workplace. - In compliance with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005, all new staff must attend at least a basic level of fire safety training. The course ensures that participants not only meet these legal requirements but are equipped with the essential understanding of fire safety within the workplace; this includes fire extinguisher types and uses, fire safety precautions, common causes of fires, and how best to act in the event of a fire ensuring the safety of themselves and others.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	2 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_safety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Dealing with fires safely and efficiently.</li>\r\n<li>	Colour coding of various fire extinguishers and their uses.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire doors, smoke alarms and sprinklers.</li>\r\n<li>	Chemical reactions and other common causes of fires.</li>\r\n<li>	Preventing the start and spread of fires.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 2, 200, '2', NULL, NULL),
(135, 46, 60, 'Annual First Aid Refresher Course', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Designed for those that have already completed either a three-day First Aid at Work or a one-day HSE Emergency First Aid at Work course. The annual refresher training will help keep first aiders’ skills up-to-date, ensuring that they remain confident and efficient when examining casualties and applying appropriate action or treatment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours. (1/2 day)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	How to manage incidents calmly and safely.</li>\r\n<li>	The examination of a casualty and further actions/treatments.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of basic life support.</li>\r\n<li>	Combination of practical and theory sessions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(136, NULL, 60, 'Food Safety', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(137, 136, 60, 'Food Safety Awareness Training', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This course is designed so that anyone working with or around food can gain a necessary general understanding of food safety practice; this includes temperature control, safe cleaning products, sanitisation and also ensuring maintained hygiene of premises, equipment and staff. Having completed the course, delegates will be able to apply this knowledge in the workplace to prevent food poisoning and the spread of bacteria and germs.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	Quiz test</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/FoodSafety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction.</li>\r\n<li>	Allergies and intolerances.</li>\r\n<li>	Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points (HACCP).</li>\r\n<li>	Temperature control (safe cooking, storing and serving temperatures).</li>\r\n<li>	Safe cleaning products to use around food.</li>\r\n<li>	Keeping your premises clean and pest free.</li>\r\n<li>	Contamination leading to food poisoning.</li>\r\n<li>	Good personal hygiene habits.</li>\r\n<li>	Sanitising food equipment and using it appropriately.</li>\r\n<li>	EU legislation and legal requirements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 3, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `categories` (`id`, `sub_category_id`, `disciplines_id`, `name`, `course_detail`, `duration`, `cost`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(138, 46, NULL, 'Emergency First Aid at Work Course (HSE) Training Course', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This HSE approved, 1 day training course is designed for individuals required to act as an Emergency First Aider at Work with a focus towards preventing situations from escalating and maintaining life until help arrives. – Designed to suit all employees such as designated first aiders or those simply requiring a comprehensive first aid course.  It is ideal for lower risk businesses, but the course can be adapted to suit the needs of any organisation if required. Participants will gain an understanding of different incidents and injuries so that they are able to treat unconscious patients efficiently and effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All training is delivered in accordance with Health and Safety Regulations and we can also offer Qualsafe and CIEH accreditation for a small extra fee.  First aid regulations (HSE) relating to the workplace will be covered as part of the course.</p>  \r\n\r\n<p>We offer the one day emergency first aid at work training courses at centres across the UK, in-house at your premises, or at a local centre of your choosing. Please use our “Open Course” search function on the right hand side to quickly find training in your area, or call today to book an onsite instructor.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Continuous Assessment</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Emergency First Aid at Work Accredited Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n <ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	First aid health and safety regulations.</li>\r\n<li>	Learn about the priorities of first aid and how to manage an incident safely.</li>\r\n<li>	Treatments of unconsciousness, Shock, bleeding and common workplace injuries.</li>\r\n<li>	Combination of practical and theory sessions to deal with first aid emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>	Learn how to administer first aid in a variety of situations. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(139, 46, NULL, 'Emergency First Aid at Work Awareness Training Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<P>Provides participants with a general understanding of first aid and how to manage incidents safely. Participants will be able to act confidently in an emergency situation; identifying the cause, alerting the emergency services and providing appropriate care until the emergency services arrive. Suitable for participants looking to become an ‘appointed person’ but should ideally be taken by all staff in order to raise the general awareness of what to safely do in the event of an emergency.\r\n</P>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Continuous Assessment throughout</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage, interact and undertake practical assessment</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Emergency First Aid at work Awareness Certificate valid for 1 year, awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	Understand the principles of first aid.</li>\r\n<li>	How to alert advanced medical help.</li>\r\n<li>	Managing an incident safely.</li>\r\n<li>	Basic life support/recovery position.</li>\r\n<li>	Provide appropriate first aid for minor injuries, choking, bleeding and Shock.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(140, 46, NULL, 'Basic Pediatric First Aid Training ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Designed for those who are responsible for the welfare of children, such as nannies, child carers, au pairs and babysitters. Training ensures participants are able to enrol on the voluntary part of the Ofsted Childcare Register and, once completed they will also gain a clear understanding of childhood illnesses including how to identify and respond to a range of emergency situations.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Assessment via continual observation</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/child-2737062_1920.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	First aid health and safety regulations and priorities.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with first aid emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>	Responding appropriately to Shock, bleeding, burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with fractures, anaphylaxis, and eye and ear injuries.</li>\r\n<li>	Understanding of childhood illnesses, including meningitis and seizures.</li>\r\n<li>	Combination of practical and theory sessions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(141, 46, NULL, 'First Aid at Work Course (HSE) ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This HSE approved 3 day first aid at work course is for individuals intending to act as a First Aider at Work. The course provides participants with the skills and knowledge required in order to give effective life support and diagnosis, to treating injuries and illnesses, maintaining care and comfort of the casualty.  - This is a high quality, intensive course that provides delegates with the vast set of practical skills necessary to respond to a range of first aid emergencies.  Once completed participants will gain a certificate, enabling them to become a designated workplace first aider in accordance with the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974.  OFQUAL accreditation is available for a small extra fee and the course can be adapted to suit any particular requirements.</p>\r\n<p>Our 3 day First Aid at Work training course is available at our centres throughout the UK or in-house at a venue of your choosing. Please use our Open Course search function on the right hand side to quickly find training in your area, or call now to book an in-house instructor.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Delivered over 3 days</li>\r\n<li>	Independently Examined via final exam </li>\r\n<li>	Accredited HSE Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	First aid health and safety regulations.</li>\r\n<li>	How to manage incidents calmly and safely.</li>\r\n<li>	The examination of a casualty and further actions/treatments.</li>\r\n<li>	Treatment of unconsciousness, Shock, bleeding, fractures, burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with heart attacks, eye injuries and general common illnesses.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of basic life support.</li>\r\n<li>	How to use First aid kits and dressings.</li>\r\n<li>	Recording and reporting injuries.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(142, 46, NULL, 'First Aid at Work Refresher Course (HSE) ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Aimed at qualified First Aiders at Work who need to renew their First Aid at Work qualification. - Designed for those who currently hold a First Aid at Work qualification and are looking for re-certification. Training recaps on all of the skills gained in the three day First Aid at Work course as well as updating participants with any new processes and responsibilities which have been introduced since their initial training. The course takes place over two days and ensures that delegates remain able to manage incidents and provide appropriate treatment safely and confidently. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul><li>	Delivered over 2 days</li>\r\n<li>Independently Examined via Final exam </li>\r\n<li>Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>Accredited HSE Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>First aid health and safety regulations.</li>\r\n<li>How to manage incidents calmly and safely.</li>\r\n<li>The examination of a casualty and further actions/treatments.</li>\r\n<li>Treatment of unconsciousness, Shock, bleeding, fractures, burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>Dealing with heart attacks, eye injuries and general common illnesses.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of basic life support.</li>\r\n<li>How to use First aid kits and dressings.</li>\r\n<li>Recording and reporting injuries.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 2, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(144, 46, NULL, 'First Aid at Work Train-the-Trainer Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>If an emergency was to occur in any situation, being equipped with the knowledge and confidence from a first aid course could help you deliver potentially life-saving assistance. These skills are also invaluable in everyday situations, which gives individuals plenty of reasons to learn first aid. You will also be equipped with the knowledge and skills to administer a wide variety of first aid techniques in the workplace with confidence.</p>\r\n<p>No matter which trainer you decide to work with, they will offer face to face support from start to finish. Utilising their expertise, the tutor can guide you through the techniques and information needed while assessing your ability to deliver first aid. Each of our trainers is also fully vetted and verified, with in-depth subject knowledge and the ability to empathise - a combination that makes their teaching methods very effective.</p> \r\n<p>As per the HSE\'s National guidelines, the First Aid Train the Trainer programme has now been replaced by a combination of two courses. So to become a certified first aid instructor you now need to have completed both the 3 Day at Work First Aid course, as well as an Award in Education in Training - both of which we provide! </p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(145, NULL, NULL, 'CIEH Level 3 in First Aid at Work ', '<p>Health and Safety First Aid regulations state that all employers must ensure that appropriate first aid provision is offered to all employees. The regulations apply to all businesses, including the self-employed and those with fewer than five employees. The course is made up of Unit 1: Emergency First Aid at Work and Unit 2: Recognition and Management of Illness and Injury in the Workplace. No previous experience is necessary to attend this course and successful completion of Unit 1 will enable candidates to act as a first aider within the workplace. This level 3 qualification is supported by the Health and Safety Executive (HSE).</p>\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unit 1 – Emergency First Aid at Work \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Roles and responsibilities.</li>\r\n<li>How to assess an incident.</li>\r\n<li>Dealing with unconscious causalities.</li>\r\n<li>Delivery of CPR.</li>\r\n<li>Treatment of choking, external bleeding, Shock and minor injuries</li>\r\n</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unit 2 – Recognition and Management of Illness and Injury in the Workplace\r\n<ul> \r\n<li>Injuries to bones, joints and muscles.</li>\r\n<li>Head and spinal injuries.</li>\r\n<li>Chest injuries.</li>\r\n<li>Burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>Eye injuries.</li>\r\n<li>Poisoning.</li>\r\n<li>Anaphylaxis.</li>\r\n<li>Major illnesses.</li>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Delivered over 3 days (18 Hours)</li>\r\n<li>Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>CIEH Level 3 Accredited Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(146, NULL, NULL, 'First Person on Scene (FPOS) Training Course', ' <p>The initial care received in the first few minutes of an emergency is often the most vital; this HSE approved course teaches delegates the skills associated with rapid assessment, stabilisation and transfer of both trauma victims and those suffering a medical emergency. The First Person on Scene (FPOS) training is an intermediate level course, although no previous experience is necessary and anyone with a desire to learn is able to attend. FPOS is fully recognised by the Security Industry Authority and endorsed by the Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh.</p>\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Determine the safety of the environment.</li>\r\n<li>	Assessing the casualty.</li>\r\n<li>	Primary survey – Danger, Response, Airway, Breathing (DRAB).</li>\r\n<li>	Following primary survey, decide between using the Basic Life Support sequence or an Automated External Defibrillator (AED) if necessary.</li>\r\n<li>	How to check a casualty’s circulation.</li>\r\n<li>	Rapid treatment of Shock.</li>\r\n<li>	Coping with trauma and helping others on the scene to do so.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<li>	Delivered over 5 days </li>\r\n<li>	Conducted onsite or offsite</li>\r\n<li>	Theory and Practical sessions</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	Receive a comprehensive handbook, assessment by an independent examiner and certification.</li>\r\n</ul>', 5, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(147, NULL, NULL, '\r\nEmergency Paediatric First Aid Course ', '<p>As of March 2017, to reach the required ratio of paediatric first aid certified staff to children, first aiders must undertake and complete an Emergency Paediatric First Aid course.  No other first aid qualification holders can be counted towards the safe number required, and to stay legally compliant, your workplace must have the necessary number of Emergency Paediatric First Aid certificate holders on site at all times. </p>\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<p>The Emergency Paediatric First Aid course is a 1-day training course that covers a wider breadth of topics and subjects than its predecessors.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Be able to assess an emergency situation and prioritise what action to take.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is unresponsive and breathing normally.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is unresponsive and not breathing normally.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is having a seizure.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is choking.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is bleeding.</li>\r\n<li>	Help a baby or child who is suffering from shock caused by severe blood loss.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Target Audience?</p>\r\n<p>Those working or wanting to work in the child care sector:</p>\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Assessment via continual observation</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Certificate Awarded on Completion. </li>\r\n</ul>', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(148, 46, NULL, 'Jauput Driver CPC Training Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This JAUPT approved course provides participants with the first aid skills and knowledge required by the 2008 and 2009 EU Training Directive, also known as Driver CPC.  The legislation states that all PCV and LGV drivers must complete 35 hours of periodic training over the course of 5 years. Participants will be able to confidently apply their newfound first aid skills on-road in a range of emergency situations.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	7 hours (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Independently Examined via Final exam </li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Accredited HSE Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n<li>	Certificate will also be uploaded to DSA database, after 5 working days of completion</li>\r\n<li>	Training may be taken any time within each 5 year period.</li>\r\n<li>	A 5 year period will commence 5 years prior to the expiry of your current Driver CPC qualification, not the date of your 35 hour training.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/highway-2606937_1920.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) procedure and when to use it.</li>\r\n<li>	Moving and handling injured people</li>\r\n<li>	Appropriate conduct for emergencies in public places.</li>\r\n<li>	Safely dealing with suspected spinal injury casualties.</li>\r\n<li>	Assessing unconscious casualties for serious conditions.</li>\r\n<li>	Correct response to minor and severe bleeding from casualties.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 7, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(149, 46, NULL, 'Anaphylaxis First Aid Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Our half day course is suitable for anyone who requires training in understanding how and when to use an auto injector in the treatment of anaphylaxis. – The course is aimed at anyone who may need training relating to the treatment of severe allergic reactions and is highly recommended for those working in the childcare sector, but not limited to this sector as is equally suitable for designated workplace first aiders. We will look at how to deal with the prevention, recognition and treatment of allergic reactions, as well as the use of auto-injectors and CPR.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	4 hours</li>\r\n<li>	Assessed throughout the duration</li>\r\n<li>	Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Certificate awarded for Anaphylaxis First Aid upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/Anaphylaxis.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with those prone to anaphylaxis.</li>\r\n<li>	Prevention, recognition and treatment.</li>\r\n<li>	The use of auto-injectors and CPR.</li>\r\n<li>	Combination of practical and theory sessions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 4, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(150, 46, NULL, 'Medical Gases Training Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This course is designed for those working in medical centres and the emergency services, including police response units and private ambulance staff. Training provides delegates with a vast theoretical knowledge of medical gases; what they are, how they are used, and how they can be safely stored and moved. Although predominantly theory, delegates will also experience some practical training elements when using the gas units and equipment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/Medical-Gases.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	What is medical gas?</li>\r\n<li>	Identify medical gases in common use and their application.</li>\r\n<li>	Understand the hazard warning signs and safety information.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of how to safely move and store medical gas cylinders.</li>\r\n<li>	Have an understanding of the types and uses of piped gases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(151, 46, NULL, 'Paediatric First Aid Train the Trainer Instructor Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p> Paediatric First Aid is a mandatory requirement for professionals whose occupation involves the care of young children. Over the duration of three days our training programme, provides participants with both a robust working knowledge of the Paediatric First Aid criteria and the necessary teaching methods/public speaking skills required of an instructor.\r\nOur course is designed in conjunction with the Early Years Foundation Stage statuary framework to provide an understanding of emergency care for children and infants in line with Ofsted’s requirements.  Therefore the course is a great investment for any company and is suitable for registered child-minders and nannies under the Approved Carers Scheme. It can also be used as evidence for employees working towards an NVQ in Childcare and Education.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Delivered over 3 days (18 GLH’s)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate valid for 3 years awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/child-2737062_1920.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	First aid health and safety regulations and priorities.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with first aid emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>	Responding appropriately to Shock, bleeding, burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>	How to deal with factures, anaphylaxis, eye and ear injuries.</li>\r\n<li>	Understanding of childhood illnesses including meningitis and seizures.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Train the Trainer Elements<h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Teaching methods and learning styles.</li>\r\n<li>	Engaging your audience.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of how people retain information.</li>\r\n<li>	Giving and receiving feedback.</li>\r\n<li>	How to present information clearly.</li>\r\n<li>	Training etiquettes (do’s and don’ts).</li>\r\n<li>	Evaluation of delegates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(152, 46, NULL, '\r\nSports First Aid Training Course  ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Ideal for anyone involved with sports and fitness clubs; from match officials, to coaches, to the players themselves. It is essential those athletes’ injuries are promptly attended to, avoiding long term damage.  Our training will not only teach participants the necessary first aid skills to deal with sporting injuries effectively and efficiently, but also enables them to accurately assess an athletes’ ability to return to their sport.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6-7 hours (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 First Aid Sports certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/first-aid.png\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction to your new role as a first aider.</li>\r\n<li>	Primary survey (initial check).</li>\r\n<li>	Communicating with the casualty.</li>\r\n<li>	Dealing with an emergency in a public place.</li>\r\n<li>	Internal and external bleeding.</li>\r\n<li>	Speedy treatment of burns and scalds.</li>\r\n<li>	Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR) and when it is necessary.</li>\r\n<li>	Assessing unconscious causalities.</li>\r\n<li>	Proper assessment and response to head injury.</li>\r\n<li>	Possible reactions to extreme temperatures/conditions.</li>\r\n<li>	Torn or stretched ligaments and muscles.</li>\r\n<li>	Asthma attacks.</li>\r\n<li>	Bone, joint and muscle injuries.</li>\r\n<li>	Assessing and treating (if possible) chest pains.</li>\r\n<li>	Emergency technique to relieve choking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(153, 46, NULL, '\r\nElectrical Rescue and Resuscitation ‘CPR for Electricians Training Course   ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Also known as \"CPR for Electricians\", is aimed at all staff looking to become competent in rescue, CPR and life-support when responding to electrical emergencies. Participants will learn how to assess victims, provide the correct emergency support, and record incidents and the treatment provided. Training is structured in accordance with Regulation 29 of the Electricity Act 1995 and ensures that those carrying out electrical work meet the recognised standards expected in the electrical industry.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6  hours (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Competency based practical and theoretical assessments</li>\r\n<li>	Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/resuscitation-4215647_1920.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	Respond appropriately to an electrical emergency.</li>\r\n<li>	Carry out an assessment.</li>\r\n<li>	Release and rescue victim safely and efficiently.</li>\r\n<li>	Manage victim whilst being aware of risks and hazards.</li>\r\n<li>	Recognise and react to an unconscious victim and one with no signs of life.</li>\r\n<li>	Competently use a resuscitation mask.</li>\r\n<li>	Provide first aid for electrical burns.</li>\r\n<li>	Communication.</li>\r\n<li>	Reporting.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(154, 44, NULL, 'Fire Marshalling Training Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p> Designed specifically for those who have been appointed to carry out the duties of a Fire Warden or Fire Marshall.  The course is certified and complies with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005. - Designed for any members of staff who are looking to become the designated fire warden for their workplace. Participants will learn about causes and effects of fires, as well as how to prevent them spreading, by learning how to implement necessary emergency procedures. The course can also be combined with our fire extinguisher practical course for a more intensive training experience to cover all fire risks.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	4 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire-marshal.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	The role of the fire marshal and responsibilities.</li>\r\n<li>	Relevant legislation and guidelines.</li>\r\n<li>	Preventing fires and the spread of them within buildings.</li>\r\n<li>	Fighting fires with both fixed installations and portable extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire hazards and causes of fires.</li>\r\n<li>	Emergency protocol, including evacuation, emergency lighting and assembly points.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire alarms, fire drills and safety training.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire risk assessment.</li>\r\n<li>	Understanding categories of fire and how they differ.</li>\r\n<li>	Meaning of the colour codes on fire extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Regular fire safety inspections and keeping a fire log.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 4, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(155, 44, NULL, 'CIEH Level 1 Fire Safety Awareness Training Course  ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>The Level 1 fire safety awareness training is designed to help employees recognise fire safety issues in the work place and understand how to react when the fire alarm sounds.  - This CIEH accredited course is ideal for delegates at beginner level, with no experience of fire safety, and would act as a great induction to enable them to move on to train at a higher level. Training ensures that delegates are equipped with essential fire safety understanding, including how to undertake risk assessments, the causes of fires, effective preventative measures, and how to use fire extinguishers.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Level 1 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Common causes of fires.</li>\r\n<li>	Preventing the start and spread of fires.</li>\r\n<li>	Effects of fires on the workplace and staff.</li>\r\n<li>	Identifying, controlling and reporting hazards.</li>\r\n<li>	The Fire Triangle (Combustion Triangle).</li>\r\n<li>	Duties and responsibilities of staff, employers and fire marshals.</li>\r\n<li>	Using and maintaining portable extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Correct protocol when dealing with a fire.</li>\r\n<li>	Risk assessment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(156, 44, NULL, 'CIEH Level 2 Fire Safety Principles Training Course   ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Allows participants to develop their basic fire safety awareness and is particularly useful for employees who have a designated responsibility for workplace fire safety, such as  fire wardens or fire Marshalls - The CIEH accredited course is ideal for those with some previous fire safety experience, who are looking to enhance their current knowledge by take responsibility for fire safety in their workplace within a specified role, such as  fire warden, stewarding or marshalling. Training ensures that delegates are aware of the relevant legislation with which they must comply, and that they are equipped with the sufficient skillset to assess and reduce/eliminate fire risks, prevent spread of fire and follow correct protocol in the event of a fire.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Level 2 CIEH Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction.</li>\r\n<li>	Your new role and the responsibilities it entails.</li>\r\n<li>	Extinguishing fires when safe to.</li>\r\n<li>	Learning the different types of smoke and fires.</li>\r\n<li>	Fixed and portable extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Complying with The Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005, and other legal legislation.</li>\r\n<li>	Routine inspections.</li>\r\n<li>	Controlling fire to prevent spreading.</li>\r\n<li>	Identifying fire hazards and eliminating them.</li>\r\n<li>	Protocol upon discovering a fire.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire alarms and evacuation procedure.</li>\r\n<li>	Risk assessment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(157, 44, 60, '\r\nCIEH Level 3 Fire Safety Risk Assessment and Control ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>this fire training course helps candidates consolidate and develop their existing knowledge of workplace fire safety. This fire saftey course will enable attendees to fully undertake their organisations full fire risk assessments. -  This CIEH accredited course is designed for those who work in low or normal risk environments, having already completed the CIEH Level 2 Fire Safety Principles, or an alternative course. Training will help staff to expand their skills and knowledge of undertaking fire risk assessments, or in assisting those who do so; they will gain understanding of why risk assessments are important, how they can be used to improve workplace safety, and how to record any checks or assessments which they complete.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 days, with an additional 6 GLH’s (Guided Learning Hours)</li>\r\n	<li>Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n	<li>Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n	<li>Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reasons for completing fire risk assessments and their importance in a working environment.</li>\r\n	<li>Fire risk controls.</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate a risk assessment programme in the workplace, or commit to an existing one.</li>\r\n	<li>Principles of fire risk assessments and linking them to real workplace examples.</li>\r\n	<li>Contributing fire risk assessment data to improve workplace safety.</li>\r\n	<li>Keeping a record of fire safety checks.</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct fire risk assessments in the workplace.</li>\r\n	<li>Applying practical knowledge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(158, 44, 60, 'Fire Extinguisher Practical Training Course ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Our fire extinguisher practical training is designed in compliance with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 and is ideal for those with no prior fire safety experience. This course will allow delegates to practice using fire extinguishers under controlled conditions so that they are able to use them safely and efficiently when required in the workplace. Because of the practical aspect of the course, the training must take place in an outdoor environment, with plentiful space.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	2 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_safety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction to fire extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Routine fire extinguisher safety checks.</li>\r\n<li>	Using the fire extinguishers (practical).</li>\r\n<li>	Practical test.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 2, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(159, 44, 60, 'Fire Extinguisher Train-the-Trainer Course  ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>This course is delivered in compliance with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 and ensures that delegates understand the need for different types of fire extinguishers, how to inspect them for damage or wear, and how to use them safely. In addition to this essential knowledge, delegates will be equipped with the understanding and skillset required to deliver what they have learned to a new audience confidently and accurately; this is a great investment for any business.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_safety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Types of fire extinguisher.</li>\r\n<li>	Using fire extinguishers (practical).</li>\r\n<li>	Theory and practical test.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Train the Trainer Elements</h4>\r\n<li>	Engaging your audience.</li>\r\n<li>	Setting delegates at ease.</li>\r\n<li>	Various teaching and learning styles.</li>\r\n<li>	Giving and receiving feedback.</li>\r\n<li>	Presenting information clearly.</li>\r\n<li>	Training etiquettes (do’s and don’ts).</li>\r\n<li>	Evaluation of delegates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 3, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(160, 44, 60, '\r\nFire Marshall Train-the-Trainer Instructor Training Course  ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Provides delegates with an understanding of the root causes, effects and impacts of fires, enabling them to act as a designated fire marshal. Delegates will also be informed of the different types of fire extinguishers, how they should be used, and what they should be used for. The course complies with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 and, as well as an extensive knowledge of fire safety, those attending this course will gain the skills and confidence required to deliver their own fire marshal training to other staff.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	Legalisation and guidelines.</li>\r\n<li>	Categories of fire and their differences.</li>\r\n<li>	Identify potential fire hazards.</li>\r\n<li>	Impacts of fire on both people and property.</li>\r\n<li>	Prevention strategies.</li>\r\n<li>	Effective emergency fire procedures and when they should be implemented.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire extinguishers; types, when they should be used, and how.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Train the Trainer Elements</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Teaching methods and learning styles.</li>\r\n<li>	Engaging your delegate.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of how people retain information.</li>\r\n<li>	Giving and receiving feedback.</li>\r\n<li>	How to present information clearly.</li>\r\n<li>	Training etiquettes (do’s and don’ts).</li>\r\n<li>	Evaluation of delegates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 6, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(161, 44, 60, '\r\nNebosh National Certificate in Fire Safety and Risk Management Training Course   ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>The NEBOSH National Certificate in Fire Safety and Risk Management is aimed at those with workplace fire safety responsibilities. Participants will leave with the necessary skills and knowledge in order to undertake fire risk assessments in low risk workplaces. They will also learn proven safety practices as well as how to prevent casualties and damage to property. \r\n</p>\r\n<br>The course consists of three units:</br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	The “Management of Health and Safety” (NGC1),</li>\r\n<li>	The “Fire Safety and Risk Management” (FC1) </li>\r\n<li>	And the “Practical Fire Risk Assessment” (FC2).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	2 Exams required be undertaking and passes to be gained. </li>\r\n<br>- NGC1: Exam “The management of health and safety” and</br> \r\n<br>- FC1: Exam \"Fire safety and risk management\".</br>\r\n<li>	Required to undertake a practical Assessment within the workplace for FC2</li>\r\n<li>	Guide tuition</li>\r\n<li>	Certificate awarded upon completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<p>The training is divided into 3 parts. NGC1, FC1 and FC2. FC2 is a practical assessment. NGC1 and FC1 consist of the following:</p>\r\n<h4>NGC1</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Foundations of health and safety.</li>\r\n<li>	Organisation of health and safety.</li>\r\n<li>	How to promote a positive health and safety culture.</li>\r\n<li>	Assessing risk.</li>\r\n<li>	Control.</li>\r\n<li>	Monitoring review, audit and quality assurance.</li>\r\n<li>	How to investigate and report incidents and accidents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>FC1</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	How to manage fire safety.</li>\r\n<li>	Principles of fire and explosions.</li>\r\n<li>	Causes of fires and how to prevent them.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire protection in buildings.</li>\r\n<li>	Managing the safety of personnel during a fire.</li>\r\n<li>	Fire safety risk assessments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 2, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(162, 44, 60, '\r\nPractical Fire Extinguisher Training    ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Our fire extinguisher practical training is designed in compliance with the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 and is ideal for those with no prior fire safety knowledge or experience. The course allows participants to practice using fire extinguishers under controlled conditions so that they are able to use them safely and efficiently when required within this type of situation.  The practical aspect of the course must take place in an outdoor environment, with plentiful space.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>The course consists of three units:</br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	The “Management of Health and Safety” (NGC1),</li>\r\n<li>	The “Fire Safety and Risk Management” (FC1) </li>\r\n<li>	And the “Practical Fire Risk Assessment” (FC2).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	2 hours. </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/fire_marshalling.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction to fire extinguishers.</li>\r\n<li>	Routine fire extinguisher safety checks.</li>\r\n<li>	Using the fire extinguishers (practical).</li>\r\n<li>	Practical test.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', 2, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL),
(163, 136, NULL, 'CIEH/HABC Food Safety Awareness Training (Level 2) Training Course', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Ideal for those working in an environment where food is produced, packaged or handled; this includes catering, manufacturing and retail. The course ensures participants are able to meet National Occupational Standards and have a clear understanding of the principles of storing and handling food safely. In addition to theoretical elements, participants will also learn essential practical aspects of food safety, including temperature control, safety procedures and ensuring safe use of premises and equipment.</p>\r\n<p>Accredited by the CIEH/HABC - global leaders in risk and compliance-based training at the forefront of the health and safety industry.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	6 hours. (1 day)</li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Accredited certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/FoodSafety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>	Understanding of current and relevant legislation.</li>\r\n<li>	Identifying hygiene hazards and food safety procedures.</li>\r\n<li>	Temperature control: refrigeration, cold/hot holding, cooking and reheating.</li>\r\n<li>	Principles of safe food storage and handling.</li>\r\n<li>	Knowledge of food premises and equipment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 6, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(164, 136, NULL, 'Allergen Awareness Training ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>On the 13th of December 2014, it became compulsory by EU law for all staff handling, packaging and working with food to be able to inform customers of allergens and ingredients. The course ensures that participants’ are made fully aware of the latest legal guidelines and that they have the skills and knowledge to confidently provide this information. Participants will also gain essential understanding of food safety procedures regarding allergens, including correct storage, packaging and labelling of food.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	3 hours </li>\r\n<li>	Expected to engage in a number of group activities</li>\r\n<li>	 Hands on Guided Tuition</li>\r\n<li>	 Certificate awarded upon successful completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/Food-Allergies.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>	The 14 allergens (and products which contain them).</li>\r\n<li>	Food labelling standards.</li>\r\n<li>	Legislation regarding allergen awareness.</li>\r\n<li>	Selling and displaying food.</li>\r\n<li>	Packaging food.</li>\r\n<li>	Food allergies and allergic reactions.</li>\r\n<li>	Symptoms of allergic reactions.</li>\r\n<li>	Difference between a food allergy and a food intolerance.</li>\r\n<li>	Understanding food allergen awareness in catering.</li>\r\n<li>	Impact of legislation on staff.</li>\r\n<li>	Responsibilities of the operator and the consumer.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 3, NULL, '', NULL, NULL),
(165, 136, 60, 'CIEH/HABC Food Safety (Level 1) ', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"cstm-dscrptn-crs\">\r\n<p>Designed to suit any participant, including those with no prior food safety experience or awareness.  The content must therefore apply to employees working both front/back of house. The course covers a wide range of essential food safety issues, - including staff responsibilities, identifying and reducing/eliminating hazards, and both food and personal hygiene.</p>\r\n<p>We are accredited by the CIEH/HABC Training Course- global leaders in risk and compliance-based training at the forefront of the health and safety industry.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"cstm-asgnmnt\">\r\n<h4>Assessment</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Half day level 1 Food Safety training course - sector specific training programmes developed to meet the needs of staff working in catering, manufacturing or retail environments. These include:</li>\r\n<li>Level 1 Award in Food Safety Awareness in Catering.</li>\r\n<li>Level 1 Award in Induction into Food Safety for Manufacturing.</li>\r\n<li>Level 1 Award in Food Safety Awareness for Retail.</li>\r\n<li>15 question multiple choice examination at the end of the training </li>\r\n<li>CIEH/HABC Level 1 accredited certificate awarded on completion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<img class=\"img-fluid\" src=\"../images/care_courses/FoodSafety.jpg\">\r\n<div class=\"prgrm-vw\">\r\n<h4>Programme Overview</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introduction and explanation.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding responsibilities.</li>\r\n<li>Identifying hazards.</li>\r\n<li>Gain knowledge of personal and food hygiene.</li>\r\n<li>How to reduce risks of contamination.</li>\r\n<li>Cleaning tips.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', NULL, NULL, '2', NULL, NULL);
